<F P=102>  FL2302175394 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2302175394 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Senate of the Republic will be convened anew. 
On 22 February, the Army commander in chief, General Raoul 
Cedras, did not answer the invitation of the alternative office 
of the chamber led by Senator Bernard Sansaricq. This 
invitation was reported; the session has been postponed to 23 
February at 1100. Sen. Thomas Eddy Dupiton says that all the 
country's authorities are concerned about the Haitian situation 
and must look for a solution to the crisis. Sen. Dupiton asked 
Gen. Raoul Cedras to guarantee the safety of the legislators. 
We should say that this session was punctuated with nationalist 
speeches. 
  For her part, Sen. Margareth Martin asked the 
parliamentarians to fill the vacuum of the executive power -- 
the vacuum created by the resignation of Prime Minister Robert 
Malval. 

