<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government, Rearmed Group Will Hold `Decisive' Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2302190994 Managua Radio Sandino in Spanish 1200 GMT 23 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2302190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Sandino </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Events" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The government and El Chacal [Jose Angel Talavera] 
will hold a decisive meeting on Thursday in Caulatu. The 
preparations for the high-level meeting, which will determine 
the disarmament of El Chacal, were made yesterday afternoon by 
Sergio Caramagna, mediator and coordinator of CIAV-OAS 
[International Commission of Support and Verification-OAS] and 
Government Minister Alfredo Mendieta. 
  The meeting with El Chacal is scheduled to be held at noon 
today [as heard] at Caulatu, the same place where the rearmed 
group last year kidnapped two Sandinist deputies and several 
government officials. Yesterday, the Army withdrew all of its 
troops from the area to facilitate the meeting. 
  In addition to Government Minister Alfredo Mendieta, who 
leads the government delegation, the other people who will 
attend the meeting are Colonel Javier Carrion, on behalf of the 
EPS [Sandinist People's Army], while the Catholic Church has 
appointed Dr. Winston Betanco. 
  Government sources reported the government delegation is 
fully empowered to solve the conflict with the rearmed men from 
the 3-80 Northern Front. 

</TEXT>

