Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 17 Feb (PL) -- Cuban President Fidel Castro 
has met with a visiting delegation of the French National 
Assembly headed by Andre Santini, president of the French-Cuban 
Friendship Parliamentary Group and the Production and Exchange 
Commission. 
  The newspaper GRANMA reports today that the delegation, on 
invitation from the Cuban parliament, will visit the country 
from 13 to 19 February. 
  According to the newspaper, the meeting with the Cuban 
president was marked by a brotherly and friendly atmosphere and 
a broad dialogue on current topics with the participants 
commenting on reports about the two countries. 
  His Excellency Mr. Jean Raphael Dufour, French ambassador to 
Cuba; Carlos Lage Davila, member of the Politburo of the 
Communist Party of Cuba; and Deputy Alfredo Guevara, president 
of the Cuban-French Friendship Parliamentary Group, also 
attended the meeting. 
  According to the newspaper, Deputy Eric Raoult, vice 
president of the National Assembly, and Deputy Pierre Mazeaud, 
president of the Commission of Constitutional Laws, Legislation, 
and General Administration of the Republic, are part of the 
French delegation, which also includes legislators Muguette 
Jacquaint, Dominique Busserau, and Gerard Tremege and Parliament 
and Foreign Ministry officials Claude Lebedel and Marie-Claire 
Gerardin. 

