<H3> <TI>   Official Stresses Leadership's Confidence in Granma Workers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2402164294 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1502 GMT 
24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2402164294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Minister Jose Naranjo, chief of the Council of 
State's Coordination and Support Staff, has stressed the 
confidence the Cuban political leadership has that Granma's 
sugar industry workers and entire people will carry out a sound 
productive response in the current harvest. Naranjo pointed out 
that this province has traditionally marked the pace for the 
sugar industry. 
  Jose Naranjo and Alfredo Enrique Pina, first secretary of 
the 
Communist Party of Cuba in Granma Province, chaired an 
assessment meeting, which discussed the development of the 
sugarcane harvest and its recovery program. The overall good 
performance of the Roberto Ramirez and Bartolome Maso Mills, as 
well as the significant sugarcane planting efforts by the Union 
of Young Communists in the province, were underscored at the 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

