<F P=100> Ecuador </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Initiates `Strict' Austerity Program </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2502043594 Quito Voz de los Andes in Spanish 2300 GMT 24 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2502043594 </F>
<F P=104>  Quito Voz de los Andes </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Voz Andes" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Quito -- Government spokesmen have reported that the 
government has initiated a strict austerity program in an effort 
to achieve the economic stability and development goals set for 
the current year. The program includes the elimination of 
investments in new projects and programs, except for those 
projects considered to be of utmost importance. 
  According to the decree issued by the government of 
conservative President Sixto Duran-Ballen, the procurement of 
new domestic and foreign loans now depends on the existence of 
specific financing. The government will not agree to any 
international commitments, agreements, or contracts without 
first ensuring the existence of funds, and commercial contracts 
will only be signed once it has been verified that dependable 
domestic or foreign financing exists to support them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

