<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Finance Minister, OCI Director Say VAT Still in Effect </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2502022194 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 1550 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2502022194 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The value-added tax, VAT, is still in effect, 
including the consumer phase of it, Finance Minister Julio Sosa 
Rodriguez has announced. Guillermo Alvarez Bajares, OCI 
[Central Information Office] director, has also reaffirmed this 
announcement. 
  Both officials have stated that the current administration 
cannot repeal a law via a resolution or decree, adding that VAT 
was included in the Special Powers Act, which gave special 
powers to former President Ramon J. Velasquez. 
  [Begin Alvarez recording] Legally, this government cannot 
modify the VAT Law. This government cannot simply say VAT will 
be canceled. This situation will be settled when Congress 
approves the draft bills the government will present, via Dr. 
Sosa Rodriguez, to meet the same objective. These projects.... 
[pauses] The economic result of these draft bills, so to speak, 
will cover the noncollection of VAT. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

