<H3> <TI>   Peace Commissioner Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2502141594 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0435 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2502141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Manuel Camacho Solis, Mexican national </F>
commissioner for peace and reconciliation in Chiapas, at San 
Cristobal de las Casas Casthedral, San Cristobal de las Casas on 
24 February -- recorded] 
  [Text] You have been following these negotiations very 
closely. Things are moving appropriately. We have already agreed 
on 50 percent of the issues presented to us today. 
  In this, we not only see the opportunity to satisfactorily 
answer the demands but it is also an opportunity to produce a 
broad affinity on the agreements for a political solution to the 
Chiapas conflict and on the peace agreements. 
  Today is Mexico's Flag Day. Today's Flag Day celebration in 
San Cristobal de las Casas has special significance for the 
negotiations. The Mexican flag allows us to: 
  1. Maintain and defend Mexico's territorial integrity. 
  2. Resolve the Chiapas conflict in Mexican territory. 
  3. Search for dialogue instead of confrontations because we 
trust Mexico and in its future. 
  4. It is necessary we reach agreements and respect each 
other to build a better fatherland. 
  This is what I had to say today. Thank you for being here. 
You are very kind. 

</TEXT>

