<F P=106> [From the "Telepress" newscast] </F>
  [Text] This morning, some 4,000 public employees, members 
of the organization that groups state workers together, took 
part in a demonstration in western Guatemala. 
  Public employees from Huehuetenango, Quezaltenango, 
Totonicapan, San Marcos, and Solola also took part in the 
demonstration, which concluded with a meeting at a place called 
Cuatro Caminos. In this way, these state employees joined 
demonstrations staged in the capital yesterday to protest the 
government's refusal to grant a 40 percent salary increase. 
  According to local reports, traffic was interrupted on the 
Inter-American Highway for about two hours. The National Police 
dispatched officers to the site of the demonstration to 
guarantee public order along the highway. 

