<H4>   Endorses Gaviria's OAS Candidacy </H4>
<F P=102> PA2502042494 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2502042494 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Azucena Lievano, from the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Excerpt] President Carlos Menem has taken advantage of his 
official two-day visit to Colombia to confirm Argentina's 
support for President Gaviria in his bid for the post of OAS 
secretary general. He even had time to speak about his heart. 
  Argentine President Carlos Menem today gave President 
Gaviria 
a strong endorsement in his bid for the post of OAS secretary 
general. Menam also announced both presidents will seek the 
support of other countries. 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified reporter] Do you think the 
role President Gaviria will play at the OAS, if elected 
secretary general, will be a good one? 
  [Menem] He would be a good secretary general for many 
reasons. The OAS, under the leadership of President Gaviria, if 
he is indeed elected, can improve its work and performance. [end 
recording] 
  Carlos Menem went on to talk about more than the OAS. The 
Argentine president, who has generated many controversies over 
family scandals in his country, confirmed not only that his 
heart is good, but also that it is still beating. 
  [Begin recording] [Menem] Thank God, my heart is doing very 
well. 
  [Reporter] Are you in love or not? 
  [Menem] I thought you were asking about the clinical and 
medical condition of my heart. 
  [Reporter] I am asking about both. 
  [Menem] Well, my heart is doing fine in both senses. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

