<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreement Reached </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2502125094 Managua Canal Cuatro Television 0440 GMT 25 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2502125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Canal Cuatro Television 0440 GMT 25 Feb 
94 </F>




<TEXT>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It was reported a short while ago from Caulatu, 
Quilali, that an agreement has been reached between the 
government and the rebels. As a result of this agreement, 
Esteban, the brother of Jose Angel Talavera, a.k.a. El Chacal, 
head of the 3-80 Northern Front, demobilized. Another important 
result of this agreement is that 100 recontras will surrender on 
2 March, and the last man will surrender his arms no later than 
8 April. 
  The government has agreed to create a provisional 
demilitarized zone in Caulatu and El Zungano, Esteli, and 
provide food, clothing, and medicines to the rebels while they 
wait for the demobilization's deadline. 

</TEXT>

