<H3> <TI>   Details of Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2502130694 Managua Radio Nicaragua Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2502130694 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Nicaragua Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] After reaching important agreements with the 
Government of Nicaragua, the 3-80 Northern Front led by Jose 
Angel Talavera, alias El Chacal, on Thursday signed a document 
to demobilize its troops. 
  The agreements reached between the rebels and the 
government, 
through the mediation of the Catholic Church and the CIAV 
[International Commission of Support and Verification]-OAS, 
establish the following main points: progressive disarmament of 
the 3-80 troops between 2 March and 8 April, demilitarization of 
the area, and former recontras joining the command posts of 
police headquarters in the municipalities of Jinotega and Nueva 
Segovia. 
  Likewise, the document signed between the government and the 
rearmed rebels establishes various social and economic 
development programs in the area. The agreements were signed 
after nearly 6 hours of intense negotiations and several foiled 
attempts in recent days. 

</TEXT>

