<H3> <TI>   Police Repress Tavapy Peasants; Injuries Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2402175494 Asuncion NOTICIAS in Spanish 24 Feb 94 pp 2-3 </F>
<F P=103> PY2402175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion NOTICIAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Juan Carlos Salina] </F>
  [Excerpt] Tavapy 1, Alto Parana -- The police reacted 
violently against the some 400 peasants from Tavapy 1 and 2 who 
partially occupied Route No. 6, nearby km 22, for a short while 
in protest over the serious economic hardships they are 
experiencing and to demand at least 1,000 Guaranies per kilogram 
of cotton. 
  Almost 100 people were injured as a result of the police 
repression. One person was seriously injured by a tear gas 
canister. 
  The long history of struggle by Tavapy peasants was revived 
yesterday when about 400 of them temporarily occupied the road 
despite a strong police contingent. They refused to withdraw 
and sustained beatings and were the target of tear gas. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

