<H3> <TI>   President Presents Popular Participation Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2102160394 La Paz Radio Fides Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2102160394 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Radio Fides Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The following is a report from the Social 
Communications Ministry: 
  Last night, in the main hall of Government House, President 
Gonzalo Sanchez de Losada presented the Popular Participation 
Law to the nation. He did so on a national radio and television 
network in the presence of an audience of guests specially 
invited by a [word indistinct] polling company for a question 
and answer session. 
  As is his custom, the president presented the law during a 
frank dialogue with the Bolivian people and explained the scope 
and benefits this law will bring to all municipalities, 
communities, and cantons. 
  [Words indistinct] of the law, he said that it promotes and 
consolidates popular participation by incorporating Indian, 
peasant, urban, and rural communities in the political and 
economic life of the country. This law will likewise improve the 
lives of Bolivian men and women with a fairer distribution of 
wealth and better administration of public funds. It will 
strengthen the political and economic instruments necessary to 
improve democracy and will facilitate and make the participation 
of the people possible. [recorded passage indistinct] 

