<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agenda For Promulgation of Emergency Fund Outlined </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2402193494 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in 
Portuguese 1600 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2402193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Social Emergency Fund [FSE] -- which is 
considered essential for the success of the economic plan of 
Finance Minister Fernando Henrique Cardoso -- will most probably 
be promulgated this week. Congress approved the FSE with just 
one change. 
  [Begin recording] [Reporter Luciane Bacellar from Brasilia] 
The FSE was approved by 402 votes of the 500 congressmen present 
for the voting. Only one change was made: The government lost 
its power to reduce the bank PIS [Social Integration Program] 
contribution. 
  Congress approved the FSE but it has yet to decide whether 
to 
implement it immediately. The voting may take place this 
afternoon. The administration needs 293 votes to implement the 
FSE immediately. The date of the session at which the bill will 
be promulgated will be decided later. Only then will the FSE be 
implemented and will Minister Cardoso go ahead with the second 
phase of his economic plan: the Real Value Unit, URV. 
  [Senate Speaker Humberto Lucena] Congress must first 
conclude 
its work so that the minister can do his part. If the amendment 
is approved we will immediately call a session to promulgate it 
because it must be promulgated at a plenary meeting. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

