<H3> <TI>   JORNAL DA BAHIA Folds, Fires Workers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2502024494 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 23 
Feb 94 Section 1 p 9 </F>

<F P=103> PY2502024494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the FOLHA DE SAO PAULO Salvador bureau] </F>
  [Text] After 36 years of activity the JORNAL DA BAHIA, the 
state's second oldest newspaper, yesterday fired about 200 
workers and folded. A communique issued by the newspaper's 
board of directors reported that the economic crisis was 
responsible for the newspaper's folding. 
  Chief Editor Isaias Raw, 62, said the newspaper had been 
operating for two years at a deficit. According to Raw, JORNAL 
DA BAHIA had an average edition of 18,000 copies (5,000 
subscribers) and was mainly circulating in the capital of Bahia 
and in the metropolitan region of Salvador. 

</TEXT>

