<F P=100> INTER-AMERICAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cooperation Agreement Between Andean Group, Aladi Viewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2402132394 </F>
<F P=103> PY2402132394 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Montevideo LA MANANA in Spanish on 17 
February publishes on page 6 a 500-word unattributed article on 
a cooperation agreement signed by the Andean Development 
Corporation, CAF, and the Latin American Integration 
Association, Aladi, which will enable CAF "to identify 
investment opportunities" in 11 Aladi member countries. 
  CAF Chairman Enrique Garcia Rodriguez told LA MANANA that 
the 
agreement will be instrumental in helping Aladi member countries 
in their integration drive. The article quotes Garcia Rodriguez 
as saying: "We believe we can play a support role in trade 
exchanges between the different integration areas like the 
Andean Group; the Common Market of the South; the group of three 
-- Mexico, Colombia, and Venezuela; the Central American Common 
Market; and Chile, which even though it is not a member of these 
groups, furthers an open policy toward integration." 
  Garcia Rodriguez noted: "Seventy percent of CAF credits are 
earmarked for bolstering private initiatives." 

</TEXT>

