<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government-Recontra Peace Talks Get Under Way </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2502000994 Managua Radio Corporacion in Spanish 2300 GMT 
24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2502000994 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Corporacion </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Five O'Clock Sharp" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Nicaraguan Government and the leaders of the 
recontras today began their first direct meeting to discuss the 
disarmament of the rebels and peace in the country's north, 
where there has been violence the past few years. Sources within 
the Government Ministry, the Army, the OAS, and the Catholic 
Church confirmed the start of the talks in village of Caulatu 
near the Honduran border. The OAS and the church are acting as 
mediators. 
  The delegation of recontras from the so-called 3-80 Northern 
Front is led by its leader, Jose Angel Talavera, alias El 
Chacal. The government is represented by Government Minister 
Alfredo Mendieta and Colonel Javier Carrion, the Army's deputy 
chief of staff. The mediation commission comprises members of 
the OAS and the Catholic Church who will verify fulfillment of 
any agreements reached within the next few days concerning the 
demobilization and disarmament of the recontras. 

</TEXT>

