<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres, 'Arafat Meet in Switzerland 29-30 Jan </TI></H3>
<H4>   Delegations Hold First Meeting </H4>
<F P=102> TA3001054794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 30 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3001054794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The PLO and Israeli delegations in Davos last night 
issued a joint communique stating that the first meeting between 
the two parties was conducted in a very positive atmosphere 
which indicated good chances for future progress. Both 
delegations established a joint formulations committee which 
held its first meeting last night. This committee will continue 
work this morning. The formulations committee will deal with the 
major issues currently on the agenda: the implementation of the 
Gaza-Jericho First agreement and the issue of the border 
crossings. This morning, the committee will report to the 
plenum on the results of the discussions. The members of the 
formulations committee are Nabil Sha'th, Abu-al-'Ala' [Ahmad 
Quray'], and Akram Haniyah, on behalf of the PLO, and its 
Israeli members are Uri Savir, Major General 'Uzi Dayan, and 
Yo'el Singer. 
  Minister Yosi Sarid warned against excessive optimism and 
explained that there were still gaps between the parties' 
positions. Sarid said that it would only be possible this 
evening to know whether an agreement had been reached. 
  Last night, Yasir 'Arafat and Shim'on Peres held a private 
meeting which lasted approximately two hours. 

</TEXT>

