<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres, 'Arafat Meet in Switzerland 29-30 Jan </TI></H3>
<H4>   'Arafat, Sarid Express Optimism </H4>
<F P=102> TA3001154494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 30 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3001154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The meeting of Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres and 
PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat in Davos -- also attended by Minister 
Yosi Sarid and Egyptian Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa -- has ended. 
After the meeting 'Arafat said that not all the problems were 
solved, but he expects an agreement soon. Yosi Sarid said there 
are ups and downs; agreement was achieved on some issues and now 
we are closer to an agreement. Arab sources told our 
correspondent Gid'on Kouts that for all intents and purposes an 
agreement has been achieved, except for some minor issues. 
Israeli members in the formulations committee said that 
understandings were reached on all issues; the two sides made 
concessions and there is a chance for reaching an agreement. 
  Foreign Minister Peres will stay in Davos until tomorrow 
morning. The contacts will be carried on tonight. 

</TEXT>

