<H3> <TI>   Peres, 'Arafat Meet in Switzerland 29-30 Jan </TI></H3>
<H4>   Musa: Accord Signing `Within Two Weeks' </H4>
<F P=102> TA3001184294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1700 GMT 30 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3001184294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shim'on Peres and Yasir 'Arafat announced that 
progress has been made in the Davos talks. Egyptian Foreign 
Minister 'Amr Musa told our correspondent Gid'on Kouts that the 
agreement will be signed in Cairo, apparently within two weeks. 
Our correspondent reports that differences of opinion remain 
only on the Jericho area issue. On the issue of the border 
crossings it was agreed that a Palestinian attorney will be 
permitted to attend the interrogation of suspects detained at 
the crossings. 
  The Davos negotiations will continue this evening at a 
junior 
level. Peres and 'Arafat will intervene if called to do so. 
Minister Peres will leave Davos tomorrow morning. 

</TEXT>

