<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres, 'Arafat Meet in Switzerland 29-30 Jan </TI></H3>
<H4>   'Abd-Rabbuh on Possible Talks in Cairo </H4>
<F P=102> NC3001183394 London MBC Television in Arabic 1807 GMT 30 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3001183394 </F>
<F P=104>  London MBC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone interview with PLO Information Department Head </F>
Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh in Davos, by MBC Anchorman Antoine 'Awn in 
London, "few minutes ago"--recorded] 
  [Text] ['Abd-Rabbuh] In fact, discussions continue up to 
this moment. I believe that these negotiations could reach 
agreement over some points, but not all of them during this 
round. Discussions revolve around the issue of the crossings, 
the Jericho area, and the settlements in Gaza. There is some 
slow and simple progress in these points. We are now working on 
finding a joint formula on the things we have managed to agree 
on. There are still some difficulties. I believe that if all 
points are not addressed during this round, we could discuss 
them in Cairo to finalize our agreement. 
  ['Awn] Mr. Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, on what level will discussions 
in Cairo take place? On President 'Arafat's level? 
  ['Abd-Rabbuh] I do not think so. Before we reach 
discussions on the level of President 'Arafat and Prime Minister 
Rabin, we need to be very close to finalizing the agreement in 
its broad outlines and even its essential details. Therefore, 
what we agree on now will form a part of the agreement that we 
must finalize at a later date. 
  ['Awn] Mr. Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, thank you. 
  ['Abd-Rabbuh] I thank you. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

