<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres, 'Arafat Meet in Switzerland 29-30 Jan </TI></H3>
<H4>   Israeli Sources: Talks Yield Document </H4>
<F P=102> TA3001202494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 2000 GMT 30 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3001202494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shim'on Peres and Yasir 'Arafat are slated to meet 
in Davos at the present time. Our correspondent Gid'on Kouts 
reports that the Israeli-Palestinian formulations committee 
completed its work and has reached a written document. Israeli 
sources in Davos say that if the document is approved by Yitzhaq 
Rabin and Yasir 'Arafat an agreement will be reached. Sources 
in the Palestinian delegation say, on the other hand, that some 
problems remain and the Israelis are retreating from promises 
they have made. 
  The document includes mutually agreed-upon positions as well 
as the positions of each of the two sides. It was reported that 
agreement has been reached on the sterile room at the border 
crossings, as well as on the issues of security roads and zones 
in the Gaza Strip. On the other hand there is only a basic 
understanding regarding the size of the Jericho area; a 
gentleman's agreement has been reached that Israel will increase 
this size as a goodwill gesture. 
  The Israeli sources assessed that the agreement will not be 
initialed tonight. 
  Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres told our correspondent that 
if 
everything is concluded this will constitute a major step toward 
implementing the agreement of principles. Peres would not 
commit himself to deadlines and dates for the implementation of 
the agreement of principles, but said that if an agreement is 
reached the road will be greatly shortened. He added that every 
side has remained faithful to its principles: Israel made no 
concessions on security issues, whereas the Palestinians 
insisted on issues relating to their self-respect and sentiments. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

