<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres, 'Arafat Meet in Switzerland 29-30 Jan </TI></H3>
<H4>   Peres, 'Arafat Agree on 12 Points </H4>
<F P=102> NC3001214194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2052 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC3001214194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 30 Jan (MENA)--Informed diplomatic sources 
have stated that during their meeting in Davos, Switzerland, the 
Palestinian delegation led by Yasir 'Arafat and the Israeli 
delegation led by Shim'on Peres have agreed on 12 points that 
were sources of disagreement. In a statement to MENA, these 
sources said that among the points on which they agreed is 
allowing a Palestinian police presence at the crossing points 
between Gaza, Jericho, and Jordan, and the flying of the 
Palestinian flag at the crossing points that lead to Gaza and 
Jericho. They also agreed to jointly search goods passing 
through the crossing points, to establish Palestinian projects 
by the Dead Sea, on joint Palestinian-Israeli projects, and to 
set up a crossing in the al-Maghtas area [site where Jesus 
Christ is believed to have been baptized] and raise the 
Palestinian flag in the area on certain occasions. 
  These sources also said that among the 12 points of 
agreement 
is that the security belt of Israeli settlements in the Gaza 
Strip should be 36 km long. They also agreed on the presence of 
joint Palestinian-Israeli security control on roads in Gaza and 
Jericho and to have joint patrols on the borders. These sources 
said that defining the size of Jericho's area was left to the 
Israeli side [words indistinct] a size of 54 kms. The sources 
expect the two sides to sign the points of agreement they 
reached in Cairo soon. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

