  [Excerpts] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres and PLO Chairman 
Yasir 'Arafat will meet in Cairo on Sunday [6 February]. After 
a further round of talks in Switzerland last night, Peres said 
he was optimistic that the differences between the two sides can 
be bridged before next week's meeting, where it is hoped an 
agreement on implementing the Gaza-Jericho First plan can be 
signed. Mark Weiss reports: 
  [Begin recording] [Weiss] [passage omitted] Addressing the 
economic forum, Foreign Minister Peres had this message for 
Yasir 'Arafat: 
  [Peres] May I tell Chairman 'Arafat, who himself 
personalizes the great suffering of the Palestinian people, that 
we on our side, on the Israeli side, are decided to enable as 
much as it depends on us to make the Palestinian story a story 
of success. 
  [Weiss] Peres praised 'Arafat's determination to reach 
agreement and said that although both sides had compromised, 
Israel had made no concessions on security issues. [passage 
omitted] [end recording] 

