<H3> <TI>   Middle East Disarmament Committee Opens Meetings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3001162694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1445 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC3001162694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 30 Jan (MENA)--A committee on disarmament 
stemming from the multilateral talks for peace in the Middle 
East opened meetings on the expert level in Cairo this 
afternoon. Ambassador Nabil Fahmi, political adviser to the 
foreign minister, is leading Egypt's team to the talks. 
  The committee will discuss various topics concerning the 
limitation of nuclear, chemical, and biological weapons in the 
Middle East. The committee, which will continue meetings for 
six days, will also discuss the possibility of establishing a 
demilitarized zone in the Middle East as well as look into 
aspects of regional cooperation. 

</TEXT>

