<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Meets With U.S. Ambassador in Tunis </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2901203494 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2901203494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] This morning, Brother Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat], 
president of the state of Palestine and PLO Executive Committee 
chairman, received Mr. John McCarthy, the ambassador of the 
United States in Tunis. During the meeting a discussion took 
place covering the latest developments in the 
Palestinian-Israeli negotiating process and the deadlock it has 
reached as a result of the obstacles placed by Israel in the way 
of implementing the Palestinian-Israeli Declaration of 
Principles agreement. 
  Brother President Abu-'Ammar has sent an appeal to U.S. 
President Bill Clinton asking him to intervene, as the agreement 
was reached under his auspices. Brother President Abu-'Ammar 
also asked for the intervention of the United States in its 
capacity as one of the two co-chairmen of the peace talks, in 
order to overcome the deadlock in the negotiations and attain 
the accurate and faithful implementation of the provisions that 
were approved in Washington. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

