<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Brother Abu 'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat], president of 
the state of Palestine and chairman of the PLO Executive 
Committee, received today Sir Michael Burton, assistant 
undersecretary of state of the British Foreign and Commonwealth 
Office, and the delegation accompanying him. 
  The peace process, the current negotiations with Israel, and 
the obstacles facing them which are being put forth by Israel 
were reviewed during the meeting. 
  The brother President leader Abu 'Ammar entrusted Sir 
Michael 
with an important message for John Major, the British prime 
minister, on the course of the negotiations and the contribution 
in overcoming the obstacles facing them. The British 
contribution to the development operations in the occupied 
Palestinian territories was reviewed in light of the talks held 
by the brother president during his latest visit to Britain. 
  Palestinian-British bilateral relations and the importance 
of 
the British and European role in general for the reconstruction 
of the Palestinian territories were also reviewed. [passage 
omitted] 

