<H3> <TI>   Israel Said Pressing for Extradition of Yasin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN3001122394 Amman AKHIR KHABAR in Arabic 29-30 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN3001122394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHIR KHABAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Paris--AKHIR KHABAR has learned from a high-level 
Tunisian source that the Israeli authorities are pressing for 
the extradition to Israel of Israeli agent 'Adnan Yasin, a 
Palestinian national. The source added that Israel might use 
him as a bargaining chip in the ongoing PLO-Israeli negotiations. 
  The source went on to say: The Tunisian authorities, which 
interrogated this agent after unearthing his espionage 
activities, do not intend to extradite him to Israel. Any 
decision in this regard is bound to be influenced by the 
Palestinian leadership's calculations regarding this issue, the 
source noted. 

</TEXT>

