<H3> <TI>   Fatah Wins Gaza Engineers' Association Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2901150294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 29 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2901150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Fatah has narrowly won the elections to the Gaza 
Strip Engineers Association, which will now be headed by a Fatah 
representative, with a deputy from the Islamic list. The 
executive committee will be run by a Fatah majority, but next 
year the Islamic list will have a majority. This arrangement 
was dictated by the need to rotate one seat. 
  Our correspondent Moti Amir reports that since the Islamic 
movements have traditionally held a majority in the Engineers 
Association, the Gaza Strip Fatah chapter views the election 
results as a victory. 

</TEXT>

