<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paper Says Israel Avoiding Agreement Deadlines </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3101082894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0605 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC3101082894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 31 Jan (MENA)--The newspaper AL-JUMHURIYAH 
says Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin's statements are 
designed to avoid meeting the April deadline to implement the 
Gaza-Jericho Agreement just as he avoided beginning the 
withdrawal on 13 December. 
  The paper adds: Israel knows how to sell the illusions of 
peace to obtain more arms deals and restore its ties with many 
countries. The U.S. pressure to end the Arab boycott of Israel 
before the latter takes any concrete step proves this. 
  AL-JUMHURIYAH points out that Israel has a long experience 
in 
prevarication and maneuvers, the most recent of which was the 
farce over a referendum on withdrawal from the Golan Heights. 
This was a move intended to confront the results of the Geneva 
summit between Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad and U.S. President 
Bill Clinton. 
  AL-JUMHURIYAH concludes: Washington apparently approves of 
this game as demonstrated by a remark made by U.S. Secretary of 
State Warren Christopher that his country, although a full 
partner to the process, will not pressure Syria or Israel in the 
peace negotiations and will not mediate unless requested to by 
both parties. 

</TEXT>

