<H3> <TI>   NCO Shot, Wounded By Unidentified Gunmen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3001150494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1330 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC3001150494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 30 Jan (MENA)-- A noncommissioned officer, 
Muhammad Darwish, of al-Minya State Security Detective Bureau 
sustained bullet wounds to the chest, thigh, and the right foot 
when unidentified gunmen fired at him today as he was on his way 
to work on al-Ashraf Street in Mallawi. This was stated by an 
official source in the Interior Ministry, who said that Darwish 
was taken to hospital for treatment. 
  Key figures in the al-Minya Security Directorate and the 
Public and State Security departments and experts from the 
various detective departments and the criminology laboratory 
headed for the scene of the incident to examine it. 
  Meanwhile, the police are making intense efforts to 
apprehend 
the culprits and the incident has been reported to the 
prosecutor's office to start investigations. 

</TEXT>

