<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Regime Forces Said To Attack Dollar Market </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2901194494 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Kurdistan in 
Arabic 1530 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2901194494 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Kurdistan </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We have received confirmed news from Baghdad saying 
that on the evening of Wednesday, 26 January 1994, a number of 
jumbo [preceding word in English] cars, affiliated with the 
Iraqi regime's intelligence service, were driven at high speed 
into a square near the Baghdad International Fair, which has 
become a market for dollar dealers. The Iraqi regime's 
intelligence forces asked the dealers to be quiet and to remain 
in their places. However, the dealers, who were aware of the 
intentions of the intelligence men, tried to escape. The 
regime's men fired at those who tried to escape, killing and 
wounding many innocent people. After gaining control over the 
area, the regime men arrested many people and left the bodies of 
the slain in the streets. Such criminal acts have exacerbated 
the miserable situation in Baghdad and increased the citizens' 
worries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

