<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Companies Buying, Selling Foreign Currencies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN3001213094 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1920 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN3001213094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 30 Jan (INA)--Several companies have begun 
mediating to buy and sell foreign currencies in Baghdad in 
accordance with the instructions issued by the Central Bank of 
Iraq in this regard. 
  A responsible source at the control directorate overseeing 
banks' foreign transfers told the Iraqi News Agency that the 
activities of these companies are confined to mediating to sell 
foreign currencies at a commission defined by the bank. He 
pointed out that these companies are not allowed to present 
direct or indirect credit offers and facilities, open current 
accounts for their currencies, accept deposits in any form, or 
present guarantees in local or foreign currencies, except 
sureties presented to the Central Bank of Iraq. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

