<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Radioactive `Leak' From Dimona Reactor Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2801150594 Cairo AL-AHALI in Arabic 26 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC2801150594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-AHALI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A serious radioactive leak has taken place at 
Israel's Dimona Reactor in the Negev desert. Responsible 
Egyptian sources have disclosed that the Egyptian border region 
may be affected by the leak. There is fear of nuclear fallout 
[tarsibat] in the area from al-'Arish to Rafah. The responsible 
quarters have instructed experts in chemical warfare to conduct 
a full survey of the border region and measure the degree of 
radiation. 

</TEXT>

