<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jordanian Diplomat Assassinated in Beirut 29 Jan </TI></H3>
<H4>   Al-Majali Comments on Beirut Murder </H4>
<F P=102> JN3001180694 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1600 GMT 
30 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3001180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The House of Representatives today held a 
session under House Speaker Tahir al-Masri and in the presence 
of Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali and the ministers. 
The House discussed a number of its agenda items. Details are 
in the following report by our correspondent: 
  At the outset of the session and before discussing the 
agenda, House Speaker Tahir al-Masri announced the death of 
Senate Member Bahjat al-Talhuni. He also denounced the wicked 
attack on late martyr Na'ib 'Umran al-Ma'ayitah, counselor at 
the Jordanian Embassy in Beirut. [passage omitted] 
  The House agreed to issue a statement denouncing this 
heinous 
crime. Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali said that the 
Jordanian Government is in constant contact with the Lebanese 
Government and will be kept informed about the investigations in 
this case as Jordan has asked to take part in these 
investigations. 
  Dr. al-Majali said: [Begin al-Majali recording] In fact, 
there have been contacts with the Lebanese Government between 
the minister of interior and his counterpart over there [word 
indistinct] on the investigations. They said that there are 
vague leads and we have asked to take part somehow in order to 
be directly informed about developments. So far there are no 
fingers pointing to any particular party. However, when such 
developments take place, we will inform the House, thank you. 
[end recording] 
  Afterwards, the House began to discuss items on the agenda. 
The House listened to the government's response to questions 
posed by a number of deputies dealing with citizens' public 
affairs. 

</TEXT>

