<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jordanian Diplomat Assassinated in Beirut 29 Jan </TI></H3>
<H4>   Lebanese Delegation Arrives </H4>
<F P=102> JN3101122394 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1100 GMT 
31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3101122394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A Lebanese Foreign Ministry delegation, led by Zafir 
al-Hasan, the Ministry's secretary general, arrived in Amman 
this morning to offer condolences on behalf of the Lebanese 
Government and people on the martyrdom of the late Na'ib 'Umran 
al-Ma'ayitah, the counselor at the Jordanian Embassy in Beirut, 
who was assassinated by criminal terrorists in Beirut last 
Saturday. 
  On arrival at Queen Alia International Airport, al-Hasan 
said: The crime that was committed was an ugly crime, and we 
strongly condemn it. We feel great sorrow over the martyrdom of 
the Jordanian diplomat because the victim was one of our 
Jordanian brothers. 
  He added: We bow with appreciation to martyr al-Ma'ayitah 
because he offered much during his mission. We in Lebanon, and 
on all levels, are doing all we can to identify and punish the 
criminals. He emphasized Lebanon's readiness to cooperate with 
Jordan in order to secure their arrest. 
  He voiced sincerest condolences in the name of 
Lebanon--president, government, and people--on the martyrdom of 
the Jordanian diplomat, and said: We offer our heartfelt and 
sincerest condolences to Jordan--king, government, and 
people--and to the martyr's family. 

</TEXT>

