<H3> <TI>   Three `Terrorists' Killed; 4 Wounded in Clashes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA3101060894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 31 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3101060894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In south Lebanon, it has been disclosed that three 
terrorists were killed and four others wounded in two separate 
incidents. Qol Yisra'el's reporter in the north says in one 
incident on Thursday morning [27 January], a group of terrorists 
tried to penetrate into the security zone and walked into a mine 
field, wounding four of them. They were rescued by local 
villagers. 
  In the other incident on Friday morning, three terrorists 
were killed in a firefight with IDF [Israel Defense Forces] 
soldiers. None of the soldiers was hurt. The clash took place 
in Wadi al-Tannur, in the western sector of the security zone. 

</TEXT>

