Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Orumiyeh, West Azarbaijan Prov., Jan 31, IRNA -- A 
Turkish Foreign Ministry official here Monday expressed Ankara's 
deep regret over the bombardment of two villages in Sar Dasht by 
Turkish jet fighters on Friday. 
  Ogur Dugan, director general at the Turkish Foreign 
Ministry, 
who arrived here heading a military delegation to inspect bombed 
regions and visit the wounded, said his speedy despatch 
indicated Turkey's deep regret over the incident. 
  The team, who arrived here aboard a military plane, is to 
visit some of the wounded people transferred from Sar Dasht to 
Orumiyeh for treatment. 
  Friday's air raid by Turkish jet fighters left nine 
villagers 
dead and 19 others wounded. 

