<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tehran Denies CIA Charges on Terrorism, Nuclear Arms </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2801130594 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1030 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2801130594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Islamic Republic of Iran described the recent 
claims of the head of the CIA about Tehran's support for 
terrorist groups and Iran's attempts to obtain nuclear weapons 
as the futile repetition of Washington's previous policies. 
  The Islamic Republic of Iran's mission at the United Nations 
issued a communique last night describing the repetition of such 
allegations as the continuation of Washington's efforts to exert 
pressure on Iran and achieve the U.S. Government's political 
motives. 
  The head of the CIA has said at a session of the U.S. Senate 
Select Committee on Intelligence that the Islamic Republic of 
Iran supports terrorism and endeavors to obtain nuclear weapons. 
  The communique issued by our country's office at the United 
Nations explains that the Islamic Republic of Iran is itself a 
victim of terrorism and that during their inspctions of our 
country's nuclear sites, the International Atomic Energy Agency 
experts have testified that the U.S. claims are false. 

</TEXT>

