<H3> <TI>   Velayati Receives Lebanon's Hizballah Secretary General </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101153194 Tehran IRNA in English 1443 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3101153194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Jan. 31, IRNA -- Secretary General of 
Lebanon's Hizballah, Sa'id Hasan Nasrallah, today briefed 
Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati on the latest developments 
in his country and in the region. 
  Nasrallah, here at the head of a delegation to take part in 
the ahl-ul-bait conference, referred to the Zionist regime's 
recent aggressions on villages in southern Lebanon, the Zionists 
new plots to stir national unity and violate Lebanon's 
sovereignty. 
  He underlined his determination to resist against the 
occupying forces and defuse their plots. 
  Velayati in return underscored unity between Islamic and 
national forces against Zionist plots and called for their 
vigilance and resoluteness. 
  He also said that he was ready to support the rightful and 
just defence of the Lebanese Muslims against the "inhumane" 
aggressions of the Zionist regime to free the occupied lands and 
restore territorial integrity of Lebanon. 

