<H3> <TI>   Peres, 'Arafat Meet in Switzerland 29-30 Jan </TI></H3>
<H4>   Musa, Peres Confer Before Talks </H4>
<F P=102> TA2901112994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 29 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2901112994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres met his Egyptian 
counterpart 'Amr Musa in Davos this morning in anticipation of 
his meeting with Yasir 'Arafat this evening. The PLO chairman 
told a British diplomat the gap between the sides is wide and 
outside intervention is required to bridge it. 
  The Egyptian foreign minister will meet 'Arafat after the 
latter arrives in Davos this afternoon, and later he will hold 
another meeting with Peres. Mr. Peres expects a tough meeting 
with 'Arafat, perhaps the toughest so far at this stage of the 
talks. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English at 1300 GMT on 29 January 
reports that "Musa told Israel radio that he intends to mediate 
between Israel and the Palestinians prior to the Peres-'Arafat 
meeting tonight. The 'Arafat-Peres meeting is due to begin at 
2100, at first alone and then later with the heads of the two 
delegations.] 

