<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Faction Calls For Escalating Armed Struggle </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN3101184394 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 31 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3101184394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Basim Abu-Sumayyah dispatch from the occupied territories] </F>
  [Excerpt] In the Gaza Strip, a previously unknown 
Palestinian faction, called the battalions of martyr Ahmad 
Abu-al-Rish, which is affiliated with the Fatah Movement, has 
announced its rejection of the peace negotiations. In its first 
statement, distributed in Khan Yunus and Rafah yesterday, it 
called for escalating armed struggle against Israel, saying that 
negotiations should be carried out through the muzzle of a gun 
and not across a peace table. The Abu- al-Rish faction claimed 
responsibility for eight armed operations against the Israeli 
Army in January. 
  Palestinian sources in the Gaza Strip say that the 
Abu-al-Rish battalions were formed following the assassination 
of Ahmad Abu-al-Rish, a member of the Fatah Hawks, by the 
Israeli secret units last November. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

