<H3> <TI>   Three Cooperation Protocols Signed With Italy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2901084494 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 0500 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2901084494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Egypt and Italy have signed three protocols on 
economic cooperation between the two countries worth $670 
million. They were signed for Egypt by Dr. Yusuf Butrus Ghali, 
minister of state for international cooperation, and for Italy 
by Foreign Minister Beniamino Andreatta. 
  Dr. Ghali had left Paris for Rome two days ago at the end of 
a conference of the advisory committee of the creditor nations 
to Egypt, which opened at the World Bank's European headquarters 
in the French capital on Monday. 

