<H3> <TI>   Debt Rescheduling Accord Reached </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2901193094 Cairo MENA in English 1320 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2901193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, Jan 29 (MENA)--Egypt and Italy have reached 
an agreement regarding rescheduling the Egyptian debts with 
Italy, estimated at approximately six hundred million dollars. 
The agreement was signed in Rome yesterday by Minister of State 
at the Cabinet for International Cooperation, Yusuf Butrus 
Ghali. By signing this agreement the Egyptian Government has 
finalized all the agreements of rescheduling debts with creditor 
member-states of the Paris Club, announced an official source at 
the Ministry of International Cooperation. 
  The source added that Ghali has agreed with Italian Foreign 
Minister Beniamino Andreatta on holding a top-level economic 
seminar including officials from Egypt, Italy and Turkey for 
exchanging expertise in the fields of economic reform programs, 
privatisation and several other economic aspects. 

</TEXT>

