<H3> <TI>   People's Assembly Members Decry Policy Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3001124194 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 24 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC3001124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-WAFD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The People's Assembly members resumed their 
criticism of the government policy statement yesterday. 
  The members said the state finds itself in a dangerous 
situation because of the spreading famous trio: unemployment, 
corruption, and terrorism. 
  The members noted the very high prices of all basic 
commodities and services, demanded a fixed, standard price for 
bread, and cautioned against the continuing rise in water, 
electricity, and medicine prices. 
  They called for social justice in the government's measures 
and for protecting and securing free medicine for students and 
workers. 
  Prime Minister Dr. 'Atif Sidqi leveled sharp criticism at 
some newspapers and described what they publish about the 
officials' corruption as "coffee shop and street talk." 

</TEXT>

