<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Denies Hamas' Involvement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2901193994 Cairo AL-JUMHURIYAH in Arabic 25 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC2901193994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-JUMHURIYAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Interior Minister Hasan al-Alfi has stated that a 
study is under way to set up special funds to provide life 
insurance for police officers. He emphasized that the ministry 
provides medical and social care to all policemen and to the 
families of martyred policemen. He noted in this regard that 
two hospitals had been built in Asyut and Tanta to offer 
services to policemen in the Delta and Upper Egypt regions. 
  Al-Alfi pointed out that the current security strategy seeks 
to modernize the police department by supplying it with modern 
equipment, weapons, and technology, step up security patrols, 
and lift the morale of policemen. 
  The minister denied that the Palestinian organization Hamas 
[Islamic Resistance Movement] is involved in terrorism in Egypt. 
He noted that Palestinian defendant Samir Isma'il Salih joined 
the terrorists in his personal capacity and that he is not 
connected with Hamas. 
  Al-Alfi stressed that efforts are being made to extradite 
the 
remaining terrorists abroad, adding that so far 23 terrorists 
have been repatriated following intensive contacts with the 
countries they were in. 

</TEXT>

