<DOCNO> FBIS3-33771 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes021_c_94013" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-021 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  1 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Governor: No Militia in Asyut, No Weapons to Citizens </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2801174094 Cairo ROSE AL-YUSUF in Arabic 24 Jan 94 p 11 </F>
<F P=103> NC2801174094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo ROSE AL-YUSUF </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Asyut Governor Muhammad Samih al-Sa'id has asserted 
that there is no militia in the governorate and that no weapons 
are being distributed to the citizens. 
  In a letter to ROSE AL-YUSUF, al-Sa'id said that the 
governorate's security forces are combating terrorism with a 
high degree of efficiency, backed by various executive, 
political, and popular organizations as well as citizens. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

