<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslim Clergy Criticized for Slow Reaction </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3001104394 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 24 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC3001104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-WAFD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed commentary] </F>
  [Text] AL-WAFD published on its first page Sunday [as 
published--the picture was in the Saturday 22 January edition] a 
disgraceful picture of German model Claudia Schiffer. Eight 
full days passed and only in Indonesia were the Muslims' 
feelings aroused. They forwarded a strongly worded protest to 
the German Government, while the Islamic institutions in Egypt 
maintained complete silence. 
  Finally, the Religious Affairs Committee of the People's 
Assembly made a move and released a statement urging the boycott 
of the House of Chanel. The statement was issued after the 
house apologized to the Muslims and pledged to destroy the dress 
that was embroidered with Koranic verses and the dress's 
pictures and films. 
  The Religious Affairs Committee discovered the tragedy after 
AL-WAFD published the story and the picture twice with sharp 
comment, appealing to those responsible for Islamic affairs in 
Egypt to move and confront the West's badness and depravity. 
  The unconsciousness of the officials in Egypt could be 
tolerated in every other respect, but not in what causes harm to 
Islam and the holy Koran. We cannot but ask the People's 
Assembly: Where have you been all these past days? We also say 
to all religious bodies and organizations, at the top of which 
are al-Azhar's ulema: Wake up. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

