<H3> <TI>   Pakistani Minister Meets With Labor Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3101163194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3101163194 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] India has told the United Arab Emirates [UAE] that 
Pakistan is indulging in cheap propaganda on Kashmir to keep a 
nonissue alive. The civil aviation minister, Mr. Ghulam Nabi 
Azad, apprised the UAE leaders of the anti-India tirade launched 
by Islamabad. He held wide-ranging discussions in Dubayy with 
the labor minister, Mr. Sayf al-Jarwan who virtually holds the 
number two position in the UAE government. Mr. Azad regretted 
that Islamabad looks at every bilateral issue through the prism 
of Kashmir, making a meaningful dialogue difficult. He squarely 
blamed Pakistan for the problem in Kashmir and said Islamabad is 
fomenting the trouble to further its own political interests. 
The civil aviation minister also said that India is not sure 
whether a commitment made by one government in Pakistan will be 
honored by the next government. He pointed out that the late 
Pakistan prime minister, Zulfiqar Ali Bhutto, had committed to 
resolving the bilateral problems within the framework of the 
Simla agreement. 
  The UAE minister, Mr. Jarwan, appreciated India's 
achievements as also the steps taken for maintaining stability 
and communal harmony. He assured Mr. Azad that the Indian 
community in UAE will be well protected. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

