<H3> <TI>   Arab League Chief Offers To Host Reconciliation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN3101201494 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1930 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN3101201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 31 Jan (INA)--The Arab League has expressed 
its willingness to host a reconciliation summit between Yemeni 
President Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and Yemeni 
Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid. It invited them and the other 
parties concerned [to Cairo] to endorse the document of accord 
recently agreed upon by Yemeni parties to defuse the crisis. 
  The invitation came in a telephone call to Yemeni Vice 
President 'Ali Salim al-Bid, who is in Aden, from Arab League 
Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid. 
  It was reported that the Arab League secretary general 
informed al-Bid of the Arab League's willingness to host, at the 
Arab League Headquarters, the reconciliation meeting of the 
parties concerned so that they may sign the accord document. 
  Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid also welcomed the participation in such a 
meeting of all the Arab and friendly sides that might want to 
attend the document signing ceremony--the parties whose 
attendance at such a ceremony is deemed necessary. 

</TEXT>

