<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice chairman of the 
Presidential Council, received in Aden today brother Badr 
Hammam, Egypt's assistant foreign minister. During the meeting, 
the two sides discussed brotherly bilateral relations and ways 
to reinforce and develop these relations. They also exchanged 
views on issues and developments of interest to the two 
fraternal countries. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice chairman of the Presidential 
Council, reaffirmed our country's interest in reinforcing 
fraternal relations and strengthening deep-rooted bilateral ties 
to serve the interests of both the Yemeni and Egyptian people 
and the issues of interest to our Arab and Islamic nation. 
  During his meeting with the Egyptian assistant foreign 
minister, brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid spoke about developments in 
the national arena, noting the efforts exerted to overcome the 
obstacles and challenges facing the march toward unity and 
democracy and a modern Yemeni state in light of the results 
achieved by the Political Forces Dialogue Committee and the 
Document of Pledge and Accord initialed in Aden. 
