<H3> <TI>   Allied Airspace `Violations' Reported to League </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN3001094194 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0855 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN3001094194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 30 Jan (INA)--Iraq has addressed a letter to 
Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid on the 
Saudi and Kuwaiti rulers' continued provision of facilities to 
U.S., British, and French aircraft to violate Iraq's airspace 
and jeopardize its security, sovereignty, and national unity. 
  In a letter sent to the Arab League chief yesterday, the 
Iraqi permanent representative to the Arab League said that 
these aircraft continued on 24-26 January to violate Iraqi 
airspace, flying from bases in Saudi Arabia and Kuwait. During 
that period, these aircraft carried out 168 hostile air sorties 
over Iraqi territory. 
  A list attached to the letter detailed these violations. 

</TEXT>

