<F P=102>  JN3101160694 Baghdad INA in English 1430 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN3101160694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] New York, Jan 31 (INA)--Iraq renewed its protest to 
the United Nations against the U.S. planes violations of its 
airspace with the intention of provocation, reconnaissance and 
dropping flares. 
  Iraq's permanent representative to the United Nations said 
in 
a letter to Secretary General Dr. Butrus-Ghali that planes had 
during January 10-20 flown 728 hostile sorties over various 
parts of Iraq in addition to dropping flares and surveillance 
flights. 
  Iraq's representative demanded distributing the letter as a 
Security Council document. 

</TEXT>

