<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fighting Spreads South of Kabul </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3101085894 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service in 
English 0800 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3101085894 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A convoy of seven trucks carrying 1,250 tents left 
Peshawar this morning for Jalalalbad. These tents have been 
sent by the World Food Program with the cooperation of Pakistan 
for distribution among the Afghan war affectees. 
  Reports from Afghanistan speak of fresh fierce fighting 
between the rival warring factions in (Chehalstun) and Gazergah 
area of Kabul. The AFGHAN ISLAMIC PRESS reported from Kabul 
that the antigovernment forces used heavy shelling and rocket 
fire against government strongholds in southern parts of the 
city. The television mountain also came under heavy fire. In 
retaliation, the air force of the state Defense Ministry bombed 
the Dostam militia positions in Bala Hesar and (Tappa Maranjan). 
Afghan sources told Radio Pakistan's Peshawar representative 
that this is for the first time in the month-long war that the 
fighting has spread south of Kabul. 

</TEXT>

